Rowe is a man who gradually begins to engage with the world around him again. This is a disturbing novel in places; a tale of coming to terms with guilt, the weight of memory, of love and loyalty. Although the main character is mild-mannered and bookish, he has a disturbing past and is suddenly motivated to try to find a future. This is not one of Graham Green’s most talked about novels, but it deserves to be. As a novel of wartime, it is fascinating as a portrait of a city which is battered, but certainly not beaten, and I am glad that I have discovered it.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5837456?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/897091170"},"likeCount":33,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":8,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:10301421":{"id":10301421,"__typename":"User","legacyId":10301421,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1593065725i/10301421.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":1062,"viewableName":"Nigeyb","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/10301421-nigeyb","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":197},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.Yt2AFbLvPJhURYmp1_xiIQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.Yt2AFbLvPJhURYmp1_xiIQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.gHq2SoboU-b1HAm11XIrdw"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:10301421"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1596212989080,"createdAt":1397035274000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1580886618146,"text":"\u003cb\u003eInnocence, patriotism, self-delusion, psychology, memory, complexity, love, deceit and heroism\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://goodreads.com/book/show/213653.The_Ministry_of_Fear\" title=\"The Ministry of Fear by Graham Greene\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eThe Ministry of Fear\u003c/a\u003e (1943) is a perfect book: accessible, clever, beautifully written, evocative, tense, and quietly profound. A palpable sense of dread and unease runs throughout the story set in the early years of World War 2 in England, primarily London.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eOn one level the book is a simple story of espionage, fifth columnists, and a hapless man who gets caught up in things he does not understand however there is far more to it than that. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe story, which starts at a sinister fete, and rattles along from the word go, also muses on innocence, patriotism, self-delusion, psychology, memory, complexity, love, deceit and heroism. \u003ca href=\"https://goodreads.com/author/show/2533.Graham_Greene\" title=\"Graham Greene\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eGraham Greene\u003c/a\u003e is on the top of his game.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e5/5\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1320421571l/824392.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"280\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1328306480l/12199779.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"280\" class=\"gr-hostedUserImg\" loading=\"lazy\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/10301421?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/905393217"},"likeCount":28,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":11,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:5283293":{"id":5283293,"__typename":"User","legacyId":5283293,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1579249711i/5283293._UX200_CR0,33,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":340,"viewableName":"Jayakrishnan","isBlockedByViewer":